'St. Georges': can't find a match, custom maybe? Closest I have are [Novel Sans](http://web.archive.org/web/20150317131928/http:/www.myfonts.com/search/novel+sans) and [Fontin Sans](http://web.archive.org/web/20150317131928/http:/www.exljbris.com/fontinsans.html); BTW, /g looks pretty out of scope regarding the rest of the lettering (thinner) so could really be a custom(ization);  
('WEYBRIDGE': [Times](http://web.archive.org/web/20150317131928/http:/www.myfonts.com/search/times))  
Note this logo is not the [current version one](http://web.archive.org/web/20150317131928/http:/typophile.com/wiki/https%3A/%252Fpbs.twimg.com/profile_images/2222983317/St-Georges-logo_rgb.jpg) and could be found as vector [here](http://web.archive.org/web/20150317131928/http:/www.stgeorgesweybridge.com/uploads/publication/file/2/Review_Easter_2014.pdf) (bottom of page 12) which I can positively identify as aforementioned Fontin Sans.
